1
00:00:01,382 --> 00:00:03,315
That is a scary stack
of books.

2
00:00:04,162 --> 00:00:06,480
Does Mommy have
to read all those?

3
00:00:06,548 --> 00:00:08,849
Of course.
That's what you do

4
00:00:08,917 --> 00:00:10,217
when you go
to law school.

5
00:00:10,285 --> 00:00:11,919
Read books and
argue with people.

6
00:00:11,986 --> 00:00:13,253
Hey, what's going on?

7
00:00:13,304 --> 00:00:15,255
We suddenly having
a bowl shortage?

8
00:00:15,306 --> 00:00:17,424
We're just trying to save
our natural resources.

9
00:00:17,492 --> 00:00:19,643
This way, we only have
to wash the spoons.

10
00:00:21,128 --> 00:00:22,796
Okay, girls, shut that off.

11
00:00:22,864 --> 00:00:24,681
Grab your homework. Bedtime.

12
00:00:29,871 --> 00:00:31,338
Hello.

13
00:00:31,406 --> 00:00:34,608
Yes, hi.
I'm looking for a young college coed.

14
00:00:34,676 --> 00:00:36,777
A law student named
Allison Dubois?

15
00:00:36,844 --> 00:00:38,612
Smooth, Joe College.

16
00:00:38,680 --> 00:00:40,781
So, are you on the plane yet?

17
00:00:40,848 --> 00:00:42,849
Yes, we just boarded.

18
00:00:42,917 --> 00:00:45,669
Hey, listen, I wanted to try
one more time to convince you

19
00:00:45,753 --> 00:00:48,088
that you don't need to
pick me up in the morning.

20
00:00:48,155 --> 00:00:51,041
I think you should focus on
your first day of school.

21
00:00:51,125 --> 00:00:52,793
Well, that's awful thoughtful
of you, Daddy,

22
00:00:52,860 --> 00:00:55,796
but it's been six days since
I've laid eyes on you.

23
00:00:55,863 --> 00:00:58,298
I can't wait to see that tan
that you got in Hawaii.

24
00:00:58,366 --> 00:01:01,268
Hawaii?
Is that where I was?

25
00:01:01,335 --> 00:01:03,437
All I remember is the inside
of a military base.

26
00:01:03,504 --> 00:01:04,688
Hey, girls, it's Daddy.

27
00:01:04,772 --> 00:01:06,373
You want to say good night?

28
00:01:06,441 --> 00:01:07,841
Night, Dad!
See ya tomorrow!

29
00:01:07,892 --> 00:01:08,875
Love you, Daddy!

30
00:01:08,943 --> 00:01:10,410
Sweet dreams.

31
00:01:10,478 --> 00:01:11,612
Did you get that?

32
00:01:11,679 --> 00:01:14,081
Loud and clear.
I'll see you in the morning.

33
00:01:14,148 --> 00:01:19,253
Yep. I'll be the one who looks
like a first-year law student.

34
00:01:28,413 --> 00:01:29,563
Hello.

35
00:01:29,631 --> 00:01:31,131
Hey, it's me.

36
00:01:31,199 --> 00:01:34,101
I'm sorry to call so early.
We picked up a tailwind,

37
00:01:34,168 --> 00:01:36,536
so we're landing at 5:00
instead of 6:00.

38
00:01:36,604 --> 00:01:38,872
So I already called
for the car service,

39
00:01:38,940 --> 00:01:41,174
so you just go back to sleep.

40
00:01:41,242 --> 00:01:45,112
Honey? Honey, what?
I just lost you for a second.

41
00:01:45,179 --> 00:01:46,780
Sorry.

42
00:01:46,881 --> 00:01:49,583
We just hit some turbulence
or something. Hold on, babe.

43
00:01:49,651 --> 00:01:51,485
PILOT
At this time I'm going

44
00:01:51,552 --> 00:01:53,186
to ask you to fasten
your seatbelts.

45
00:01:53,237 --> 00:01:54,821
Joe, what's going on?
Is everything okay?

46
00:01:54,889 --> 00:01:56,723
Uh, everything's fine, sweetie.

47
00:01:56,791 --> 00:02:00,027
Just a little bumpy.

48
00:02:01,195 --> 00:02:04,364
Joe, what's going on?
Talk to me!

49
00:02:04,415 --> 00:02:08,535
I love you, Allison!
I love you very...!

50
00:02:11,739 --> 00:02:14,141
Joe! Joe, Joe?!

51
